        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:03PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 503 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hisega, or 8 miles west of Rapid City, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Rapid City, Johnson Siding, Hisega, and Pactola
Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
